        <num>CCRP 335</num>
        <heading>335.  Rule to show cause; bond forfeiture</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 335.  Rule to show cause; bond forfeiture
If the defendant fails to make an appearance and has not been surrendered or
constructively surrendered within one hundred eighty days of the execution of the certificate
that notice of warrant for arrest was sent, the prosecuting attorney may file a rule to show
cause requesting that a bond forfeiture judgment be rendered.  The rule to show cause shall
be mailed to the defendant and served on all other parties against whom a judgment is
sought.  The rule to show cause shall be set for a contradictory hearing.  The time period for
filing a rule to show cause to obtain a judgment of bond forfeiture shall be within five years
after the notice of warrant for arrest is sent.</p>
        </content>
